om/erudite.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Wizard - Finally found my class</span><hr size=1> I think that perhaps we should add forums for standard grouping strategy and generic raid basics under the &quot;strategies and tactics&quot; header.<br>
<br>
Lots of good posts on your topic are buried deep in general discussion, or have timed out.  The basics are med as much as possible, never reach FM, try to have enough mana to deal with what you can reasonably expect to see (so don't feel compelled to nuke away until you are low).  Don't get agro.  Nuke from about half life to run mode.  <br>
<br>
Did I mention assist, don't get agro, don't run around if you do get agro.  Sometimes it is best to stand next to the thing so it will hit you a few times and go back to the taunting tank without ever running out of their weapon attacks.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushizzanidiot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShizzaNidiot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/1/02 1:11:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12324.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Wizard - Finally found my class</span><hr size=1> A little trick that will immensely help the way that groups will feel about grouping with you:<br>
<br>
Announce to the group when you join that you will ration your mana for their pull rate.  Then, do so.<br>
<br>
As a Wizie, you're kindof an insurance policy for the group.  You'll have evac, and the group will trust that you'll always save enough mana to evac when necessary.<br>
<br>
You'll have stuns, so when the chanter or cleric or whoever overaggro's, you can toss a stun on the monster to give the tank that extra critical couple of seconds to regain aggro.<br>
<br>
You can even do some crowd control...when you have to.  No bard or chanter?  On a multiple pull, wait a second for tank to get good aggro on primary mob, then toss an AE on the pile.  This will sufficiently (usually) anger the secondary mob enough for him to come beat on you.  Fine, drag him off to the side, out of melee range (very important), and root his ass.  And keep him rooted until the group is ready for him.<br>
<br>
And, probably the most important aspect for the rest of the group in having a wizie there is that you have the singular ability to burn a monster to the ground quicker than anyone else can if there is a problem.  There's a fine line between when you go this route, and when you evac.  You'll learn when to make the judgement call.<br>
<br>
So, to sum up...ration your mana.  There's nothing more useless than a wizie with no mana.<br>
<br>
Obviously, contribute to the group with damage as much as possible within these contraints...you may find, that in fast pull groups, you can only afford to nuke once on every other mob in order to keep your mana up...fine.  Slow pull group, you might can nuke every fight.  Fine.  The key is to adjust yourself to the group you're in.<br>
<br>
Shizz<br>
